<p>Your cablegram No. 24. [1] My cablegram No. 344 [2] points in which are covered by Prime Ministerâ€™s cable to President [3] and 359 [4] were sent merely to inform Mr. Casey [5] of what I have telegraphed.</p>

<p>I did not intend any personal views of mine should be conveyed to Sumner Welles [6] or the President.</p>

<p>You however are on the spot and I have such complete confidence in your judgement that I entirely accept the course you have adopted.</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

